TITLE: REPLICASET Transition to SHARDED (Single Shard)
DESCRIPTION: This configuration shows the first step in transitioning a REPLICASET to a sharded cluster. The `cluster_type` is changed to `SHARDED` while maintaining a single `replication_specs` block. This effectively converts the replica set into a single-shard sharded cluster. After this change is applied, the application clients must be restarted before adding additional shards.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/guides/advanced-cluster-new-sharding-schema.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "mongodbatlas_advanced_cluster" "test" {
    project_id   = var.project_id
    name         = "ReplicaSetTransition"
    cluster_type = "SHARDED"

    replication_specs {
        region_configs {
            electable_specs {
                instance_size = "M30"
                node_count    = 3
            }
            provider_name = "AZURE"
            priority      = 7
            region_name   = "US_EAST"
        }
    }
}
```

