TITLE: Create Single-Region Advanced Cluster - Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to create a single-region MongoDB Atlas advanced cluster using the mongodbatlas_advanced_cluster resource. It defines the project ID, cluster name, cluster type, and replication specifications, including the region configuration for AWS US_EAST_1 with electable and analytics nodes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/resources/advanced_cluster (preview provider 2.0.0).md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "mongodbatlas_advanced_cluster" "test" {
  project_id   = "PROJECT ID"
  name         = "NAME OF CLUSTER"
  cluster_type = "REPLICASET"
  replication_specs = [
    {
      region_configs = [
        {
          electable_specs = {
            instance_size = "M10"
            node_count    = 3
          }
          analytics_specs = {
            instance_size = "M10"
            node_count    = 1
          }
          provider_name = "AWS"
          priority      = 7
          region_name   = "US_EAST_1"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

