TITLE: Creating a Resource Policy for IP Access List in Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform code defines a resource policy to forbid access from any IP address (0.0.0.0/0) for project IP access list modifications. It uses the `mongodbatlas_resource_policy` resource and requires the `org_id`, `name`, and `policies` attributes to be defined. The `policies` attribute includes a `body` containing the Cedar policy.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/resources/resource_policy.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "mongodbatlas_resource_policy" "project_ip_access_list" {
  org_id      = var.org_id
  name        = "forbid-access-from-anywhere"
  description = "Forbids access from anywhere"

  policies = [
    {
      body = <<EOF
        forbid (
                principal,
                action == ResourcePolicy::Action::"project.ipAccessList.modify",
                resource
        )
                when {
                context.project.ipAccessList.contains(ip("0.0.0.0/0"))
        };
EOF
    },
  ]
}
```

