TITLE: Create automated restore job using Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform configuration creates an automated restore job. It requires a MongoDB Atlas cluster and a cloud provider snapshot. The restore job automatically restores the snapshot to the specified target cluster within the target project.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/resources/cloud_backup_snapshot_restore_job.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "mongodbatlas_advanced_cluster" "my_cluster" {
  project_id     = "<PROJECT-ID>"
  name           = "MyCluster"
  cluster_type   = "REPLICASET"
  backup_enabled = true # enable cloud backup snapshots

  replication_specs {
    region_configs {
      priority      = 7
      provider_name = "AWS"
      region_name   = "EU_WEST_2"
