TITLE: Defining a Cedar Policy Set for Cloud Region in Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform code defines a Cedar policy set that forbids cluster modifications in the `gcp:us-east1` region. It uses the `cedar_policyset` data source to define the policy.  This data source converts the policy configuration into a textual representation that can be used as the `body` of a resource policy.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/resources/resource_policy.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
data "cedar_policyset" "cloud_region" {
  policy {
    any_principal = true
    effect        = "forbid"
    action = {
      type = " ResourcePolicy::Action"
      id   = "cluster.modify"
    }
    any_resource = true
    when {
      text = "context.cluster.regions.contains(ResourcePolicy::Region::\"gcp:us-east1\")"
    }
  }
}
```

