TITLE: Configuring Independent Shard Scaling in MongoDB Atlas with Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to configure a sharded MongoDB Atlas cluster using Terraform, where each shard is represented by a unique `replication_specs` element. This allows for independent scaling of each shard. The example sets the instance size for both shards to M30.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/guides/advanced-cluster-new-sharding-schema.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "mongodbatlas_advanced_cluster" "test" {
  project_id   = var.project_id
  name         = "ShardedCluster"
  cluster_type = "SHARDED"

  replication_specs { # first shard
    region_configs {
      electable_specs {
        instance_size = "M30"
        node_count    = 3
      }
      provider_name = "AWS"
      priority      = 7
      region_name   = "EU_WEST_1"
    }
  }

  replication_specs { # second shard
    region_configs {
      electable_specs {
        instance_size = "M30"
        node_count    = 3
      }
      provider_name = "AWS"
      priority      = 7
      region_name   = "EU_WEST_1"
    }
  }
}
```

