TITLE: SHARDED Cluster Migration (New)
DESCRIPTION: This configuration demonstrates the new sharding configuration for a SHARDED cluster, replacing the `num_shards` attribute with multiple `replication_specs` blocks. Each `replication_specs` block represents a single shard.  This change is required to use the independent shard scaling and auto-scaling per shard features.  These 2 changes must be done at the same time.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/guides/advanced-cluster-new-sharding-schema.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "mongodbatlas_advanced_cluster" "test" {
  project_id   = var.project_id
  name         = "SymmetricShardedCluster"
  cluster_type = "SHARDED"

  replication_specs { # first shard
    region_configs {
      electable_specs {
        instance_size = "M30"
        disk_iops = 3000
        node_count    = 3
      }
      provider_name = "AWS"
      priority      = 7
      region_name   = "EU_WEST_1"
    }
  }

  replication_specs { # second shard
    region_configs {
      electable_specs {
        instance_size = "M30"
        disk_iops = 3000
        node_count    = 3
      }
      provider_name = "AWS"
      priority      = 7
      region_name   = "EU_WEST_1"
    }
  }
}
```

