TITLE: Automated Restore Job Configuration - Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform configuration creates an automated restore job from a cloud backup snapshot. It requires a pre-existing cluster, snapshot, and specifies the target cluster and project ID for the automated restore. It depends on mongodbatlas_cloud_provider_snapshot.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/resources/cloud_provider_snapshot_restore_job.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "mongodbatlas_advanced_cluster" "my_cluster" {
  project_id     = "<PROJECT-ID>"
  name           = "MyCluster"
  cluster_type   = "REPLICASET"
  backup_enabled = true # enable cloud backup snapshots

  replication_specs {
    region_configs {
      priority      = 7
      provider_name = "AWS"
      region_name   = "EU_WEST_2"
      electable_specs {
        instance_size = "M10"
        node_count    = 3
      }
    }
  }
}

resource "mongodbatlas_cloud_provider_snapshot" "test" {
  project_id        = mongodbatlas_advanced_cluster.my_cluster.project_id
  cluster_name      = mongodbatlas_advanced_cluster.my_cluster.name
  description       = "myDescription"
  retention_in_days = 1
}

resource "mongodbatlas_cloud_provider_snapshot_restore_job" "test" {
  project_id      = mongodbatlas_cloud_provider_snapshot.test.project_id
  cluster_name    = mongodbatlas_cloud_provider_snapshot.test.cluster_name
  snapshot_id     = mongodbatlas_cloud_provider_snapshot.test.snapshot_id
  delivery_type_config   {
    automated           = true
    target_cluster_name = "MyCluster"
    target_project_id   = "5cf5a45a9ccf6400e60981b6"
  }
  depends_on = [mongodbatlas_cloud_provider_snapshot.test]
}
```

