TITLE: Creating Online Archive with Date Criteria in Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform configuration creates an online archive for a MongoDB collection using date-based criteria. It specifies the project ID, cluster name, database name, and collection name. It also defines partition fields and an archiving schedule. The archive moves data older than 5 days from the 'dateField'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/resources/online_archive.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "mongodbatlas_online_archive" "test" {
    project_id   = var.project_id
    cluster_name = var.cluster_name
    coll_name    = var.collection_name
    db_name      = var.database_name

    partition_fields {
        field_name = "dateField"
        order = 0
    }

    partition_fields {
        field_name = "firstName"
        order = 1
    }

    partition_fields {
        field_name = "lastName"
        order = 2
    }

    criteria {
        type = "DATE"
        date_field = "dateField"
        expire_after_days = 5
    }

    schedule {
        type = "DAILY"
