TITLE: Upgrading Instance Size for a Specific Shard in MongoDB Atlas with Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to upgrade the instance size of a specific shard in a sharded MongoDB Atlas cluster using Terraform. It defines an upgraded instance size of M40 for the first shard while preserving the M30 instance size for the second shard. It uses `replication_specs` to configure each shard independently.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/guides/advanced-cluster-new-sharding-schema.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "mongodbatlas_advanced_cluster" "test" {
  project_id   = var.project_id
  name         = "ShardedCluster"
  cluster_type = "SHARDED"

  replication_specs { # first shard upgraded to M40
    region_configs {
      electable_specs {
        instance_size = "M40"
        node_count    = 3
      }
      provider_name = "AWS"
      priority      = 7
      region_name   = "EU_WEST_1"
    }
  }

  replication_specs { # second shard preserves M30
    region_configs {
      electable_specs {
        instance_size = "M30"
        node_count    = 3
      }
      provider_name = "AWS"
      priority      = 7
      region_name   = "EU_WEST_1"
    }
  }
}
```

