TITLE: Defining a Cedar Policy Set for Cloud Region in Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform data source defines a Cedar policy set that forbids cluster modification in the "gcp:us-east1" region.  It sets `any_principal` and `any_resource` to `true` and uses the `contains` function in the `when` block to check the cluster regions. The `effect` is set to "forbid".
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/data-sources/resource_policies.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
data "cedar_policyset" "cloud_region" {
  policy {
    any_principal = true
    effect        = "forbid"
    action = {
      type = " ResourcePolicy::Action"
      id   = "cluster.modify"
    }
    any_resource = true
    when {
      text = "context.cluster.regions.contains(ResourcePolicy::Region::\"gcp:us-east1\"")"
    }
  }
}
```

