TITLE: Replication Specs Precondition - Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines a precondition within a Terraform resource to ensure that either the `replication_specs_new` or the original `replication_specs` variable is used, but not both. It validates the input configuration to avoid conflicts between the old and new variable schemes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/examples/migrate_cluster_to_advanced_cluster/module_maintainer/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
precondition {
      condition     = !((local.use_new_replication_specs && length(var.replication_specs) > 0) || (!local.use_new_replication_specs && length(var.replication_specs) == 0))
      error_message = "Must use either replication_specs_new or replication_specs, not both."
    }
```

