TITLE: Creating a MongoDB Atlas Database User
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to create a MongoDB Atlas database user with specified username, password, project ID, authentication database name, and roles.  It also shows how to define labels for the user.  Dependencies include the MongoDB Atlas provider and a valid project ID.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/data-sources/database_user.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "mongodbatlas_database_user" "test" {
  username           = "test-acc-username"
  password           = "test-acc-password"
  project_id         = "<PROJECT-ID>"
  auth_database_name = "admin"

  roles {
    role_name     = "readWrite"
    database_name = "admin"
  }

  roles {
    role_name     = "atlasAdmin"
    database_name = "admin"
  }

  labels {
    key   = "key 1"
    value = "value 1"
  }
  labels {
    key   = "key 2"
    value = "value 2"
  }
}

data "mongodbatlas_database_user" "test" {
  project_id = mongodbatlas_database_user.test.project_id
  username   = mongodbatlas_database_user.test.username
}
```

