TITLE: Configuring Auditing with mongodbatlas_auditing Resource Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform resource configures auditing settings for a MongoDB Atlas project, including the project ID, audit filter, authorization success flag, and enablement status. The audit filter is a JSON string that specifies the events to audit.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/data-sources/auditing.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "mongodbatlas_auditing" "test" {
	project_id                  = "<project-id>"
	audit_filter                = "{ 'atype': 'authenticate', 'param': {   'user': 'auditAdmin',   'db': 'admin',   'mechanism': 'SCRAM-SHA-1' }}"
	audit_authorization_success = false
	enabled                     = true
}
```

