TITLE: Ignoring Autoscaling Changes in Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform code snippet demonstrates how to use a lifecycle ignore customization to prevent Terraform from reverting changes made by Atlas autoscaling. It ignores changes to `disk_size_gb` and `instance_size` within a replica set to avoid unintended scaling back to the original values defined in the configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/resources/advanced_cluster.md#_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
// Example: ignore disk_size_gb and instance_size changes in a replica set
lifecycle {
  ignore_changes = [
    replication_specs[0].region_configs[0].electable_specs[0].disk_size_gb,
    replication_specs[0].region_configs[0].electable_specs[0].instance_size,
    replication_specs[0].region_configs[0].electable_specs[0].disk_iops // instance_size change can affect disk_iops in case that you are using it
  ]
}

```

