TITLE: Data Source: Cedar Policy Set Definition (Terraform)
DESCRIPTION: Defines a `cedar_policyset` data source that creates a policy to forbid cluster modification in a specific cloud region (gcp:us-east1). The policy is configured to apply to any principal and any resource, with a condition based on the cluster's regions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/data-sources/resource_policy.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
data "cedar_policyset" "cloud_region" {
  policy {
    any_principal = true
    effect        = "forbid"
    action = {
      type = " ResourcePolicy::Action"
      id   = "cluster.modify"
    }
    any_resource = true
    when {
      text = "context.cluster.regions.contains(ResourcePolicy::Region::\"gcp:us-east1\")"
    }
  }
}
```

