TITLE: Migrating Tags Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to migrate the `tags` block to a map format. This involves converting each tag block into a key-value pair within a map. It also shows the syntax for keys containing spaces and using expressions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/resources/advanced_cluster (preview provider 2.0.0).md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
tags {
  key   = "env"
  value = "dev"
}
tags {
  key   = "tag 2"
  value = "val"
}
tags {
  key   = var.tag_key
  value = "another_val"
}

```

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
tags = {
  env           = "dev"         # key strings without blanks can be enclosed in quotes but not required
  "tag 2"       = "val"         # enclose key strings with blanks in quotes
  (var.tag_key) = "another_val" # enclose key expressions in brackets so they can be evaluated
}
```

