TITLE: Creating an Alert Configuration with Metric Threshold
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to create an alert configuration with a metric threshold using the `mongodbatlas_alert_configuration` resource. It defines an alert that triggers when the `ASSERT_REGULAR` metric goes below 99.0.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/resources/alert_configuration.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
resource "mongodbatlas_alert_configuration" "test" {
  project_id = "<PROJECT-ID>"
  event_type = "OUTSIDE_METRIC_THRESHOLD"
  enabled    = true

  notification {
    type_name     = "GROUP"
    interval_min  = 5
    delay_min     = 0
    sms_enabled   = false
    email_enabled = true
    roles         = ["GROUP_CLUSTER_MANAGER"]
  }

  matcher {
    field_name = "HOSTNAME_AND_PORT"
    operator   = "EQUALS"
    value      = "SECONDARY"
  }

  metric_threshold_config {
    metric_name = "ASSERT_REGULAR"
    operator    = "LESS_THAN"
    threshold   = 99.0
    units       = "RAW"
    mode        = "AVERAGE"
  }
}
```

