TITLE: Ignore Changes with Lifecycle Customization - Analytics Specs - Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform configuration demonstrates how to use lifecycle ignore customizations to prevent unintended changes when enabling auto-scaling for analytics nodes in MongoDB Atlas. By ignoring changes to `disk_size_gb`, `instance_size`, and `disk_iops` attributes, Terraform will not revert automatically scaled values back to the original configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/resources/advanced_cluster (preview provider 2.0.0).md#_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
// Example: ignore disk_size_gb and instance_size changes in a replica set
lifecycle {
  ignore_changes = [
    replication_specs[0].region_configs[0].analytics_specs.disk_size_gb,
    replication_specs[0].region_configs[0].analytics_specs.instance_size,
    replication_specs[0].region_configs[0].analytics_specs.disk_iops // instance_size change can affect disk_iops in case that you are using it
  ]
}
```

