TITLE: Create Custom DB Role resource using Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to create a `mongodbatlas_custom_db_role` resource using Terraform. It defines a custom role named 'myCustomRole' with 'UPDATE' and 'INSERT' actions on any database and all collections.  Requires a valid project ID.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mongodb/terraform-provider-mongodbatlas/blob/master/docs/data-sources/custom_db_role.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
resource "mongodbatlas_custom_db_role" "test_role" {
  project_id = "<PROJECT-ID>"
  role_name  = "myCustomRole"

  actions {
    action = "UPDATE"
    resources {
      collection_name = ""
      database_name   = "anyDatabase"
    }
  }
  actions {
    action = "INSERT"
    resources {
      collection_name = ""
      database_name   = "anyDatabase"
    }
  }
}
```

